personnel to Launch Bay shelters.

39
00:02:59,137 --> 00:03:01,973
- It is a magnificent sight, isn't it?
- [SCOFFS]

40
00:03:02,140 --> 00:03:04,601
- It's just a bluff.
- A bluff?

41
00:03:04,767 --> 00:03:09,063
It's already quite clear that we have
no chance of winning this conflict.

42
00:03:09,147 --> 00:03:14,694
And that the wisest course action, at this point, would
be to surrender, rather than prolong it further.

43
00:03:15,236 --> 00:03:19,490
However, our own technological
resources are not unimpressive.

44
00:03:19,574 --> 00:03:24,120
Imagine what heights we and the Dezalg
might achieve, were our forces to join.

45
00:03:24,204 --> 00:03:27,665
To that end, we already have a faction,
working within the military...

46
00:03:27,749 --> 00:03:29,626
making contact with
them on our behalf.

47
00:03:29,918 --> 00:03:32,921
Hmmm... but what about B.D.?

48
00:03:33,087 --> 00:03:36,257
B.D. isn't the only
soldier out there.

49
00:03:36,341 --> 00:03:40,011
And with enough money, one
can always buy another one.

50
00:04:02,492 --> 00:04:06,079
[COMPUTER BEEPS]

51
00:04:06,871 --> 00:04:09,832
Wait! Feed it back again.

52
00:04:09,999 --> 00:04:13,836
There! Look how the power barrel
is focusing at one point.

53
00:04:13,920 --> 00:04:15,964
There ~i~is~b~ an unidentified section.

54
00:04:16,756 --> 00:04:20,385
There's definitely a link between
Section B and Eve's ghost, Major.

55
00:04:20,468 --> 00:04:23,680
The power vectors are matched,
and directly proportional.

56
00:04:23,763 --> 00:04:28,101
As the output continues to increase,
Tokyo Base is bound to be affected.

57
00:04:28,268 --> 00:04:32,814
That's fine. If that happens, then
Yahagi is bound to notice it.

58
00:04:32,897 --> 00:04:34,857
Which will force his hand.

59
00:04:34,941 --> 00:04:37,694
Keep scanning the unidentified
sections, Nakao.

60
00:04:37,860 --> 00:04:41,656
- Yes, sir.
- And you, Lieutenant. Find Yahagi.

61
00:04:41,823 --> 00:04:43,574
Yes, sir!

62
00:04:43,658 --> 00:04:46,119
I won't fail you, sir.
Not again.

63
00:04:46,452 --> 00:04:48,371
[DISTANT TRAIN SOUNDS]

64
00:04:57,046 --> 00:05:01,551
[DISTANT POLICE SIREN]

65
00:05:05,680 --> 00:05:10,143
Our new top priority is resolving the
Tomomi Murashita murder investigation.

66
00:05:10,226 --> 00:05:13,271
The murderer, Shogo Yahagi,
must be brought to justice.

67
00:05:13,438 --> 00:05:14,272
All: Yes, sir!

68
00:05:14,439 --> 00:05:16,232
But, why the rush now, sir?

69
00:05:16,399 --> 00:05:18,026
Why now?!

70
00:05:18,568 --> 00:05:20,278
- Owww!
- [GASPS]

71
00:05:21,070 --> 00:05:25,158
It's been half a year, six full months,
that you've been searching! Just find him!

72
00:05:25,325 --> 00:05:30,538
Uhhh... I... I'm sorry, Lieutenant.
We'll do everything we can!

73
00:05:30,705 --> 00:05:32,123
Then get moving, damnit!

74
00:05:32,290 --> 00:05:33,666
All: Yes, sir!

75
00:05:33,875 --> 00:05:36,002
[HEARTBEATS]

76
