Halt! Halt, or else I'll shoot!

106
00:08:58,120 --> 00:09:01,082
- Is that nice gun for me? Thanks!
- Ahh!

107
00:09:01,249 --> 00:09:03,125
[SHARP GROAN]

108
00:09:08,047 --> 00:09:09,382
Cape: \"Kamikaze Squad Leader\"

109
00:09:10,049 --> 00:09:12,426
[STRANGLED GROAN]

110
00:09:14,387 --> 00:09:16,973
- Sign: \"Safety First\"
- Jayce: Guts, scrap the car!

111
00:09:17,139 --> 00:09:21,561
Guts: OK! You got it!
[GRUNTS WITH EFFORT]

112
00:09:24,689 --> 00:09:26,023
Shirt: \"Blaze\"

113
00:09:31,571 --> 00:09:33,990
Score!

114
00:09:36,450 --> 00:09:42,331
Code F. You are to leak the information through
one of our civilian sources at 1500 hours.

115
00:09:42,415 --> 00:09:46,544
I'll send two Garlands. I want Yahagi,
not apologies, Lieutenant!

116
00:09:46,711 --> 00:09:49,088
Right. I'll take care of it
personally, Major.

117
00:09:49,922 --> 00:09:51,924
I have a new update, sir.

118
00:09:52,008 --> 00:09:55,011
A review of Dezalg operations
over the past six months...

119
00:09:55,094 --> 00:09:59,015
indicates their focus thus far has all
been concentrated on two points:

120
00:09:59,098 --> 00:10:01,475
The first being our infrastructure,
and the second being...

121
00:10:01,559 --> 00:10:04,687
the unidentified section of
the Bahamut program Eve.

122
00:10:04,770 --> 00:10:06,689
If we can acquire what
the enemy wants...

123
00:10:06,772 --> 00:10:10,192
we may be able to find a weakness
that we could use against them.

124
00:10:10,359 --> 00:10:13,195
- The unidentified section again.
- [COMMUNICATOR TONE]

125
00:10:13,362 --> 00:10:17,867
