is compromised.

128
00:10:24,373 --> 00:10:26,292
We don't have a moment to lose.

129
00:10:26,459 --> 00:10:28,669
Yes, sir.

130
00:10:30,963 --> 00:10:32,632
[DRAMATIC ACTION MUSIC]

131
00:10:32,798 --> 00:10:36,427
- Dau One to Leader. Enemy units confirmed.
- Dau Two, I see them too.

132
00:10:36,594 --> 00:10:40,473
- They're all around us. - Go to instruments.
Switch to single-line formation.

133
00:10:40,640 --> 00:10:41,932
- Roger. - Roger.

134
00:10:44,977 --> 00:10:46,896
- The Dau Unit!
- Don't worry about them!

135
00:10:46,979 --> 00:10:48,397
- Formation X!
- Roger! - Roger!

136
00:10:48,564 --> 00:10:52,693
Fire all missiles! And after firing,
return to airspace at full speed!

137
00:10:53,736 --> 00:10:56,447
Sir! Multiple enemy fighters
directly ahead!

138
00:10:57,782 --> 00:11:01,035
Our fighters have come into contact
with carrier-based enemy elements.

139
00:11:01,202 --> 00:11:04,455
The enemy carrier is now in range
of our main guns, Admiral!

140
00:11:04,622 --> 00:11:07,750
We'll engage with
cannon and torpedo.

141
00:11:07,833 --> 00:11:10,419
All ships, target that carrier.

142
00:11:10,586 --> 00:11:14,465
All ships, prepare to engage
torpedoes with energy cannons.

143
00:11:14,548 --> 00:11:18,469
Target the enemy carrier.
Distance: two-zero, two-zero.

144
00:11:18,552 --> 00:11:19,929
Commence energy injection.

145
00:11:20,096 --> 00:11:22,598
Steady as you go!
Automated tracking devices, ready.

146
00:11:22,765 --> 00:11:25,935
Enemy units closing fast! Anti-aircraft
cannons, put up screening fire!

147
00:11:26,102 --> 00:11:27,853
All missile tubes launch.

148
00:11:31,190 --> 00:11:33,609
Enemy unit over the bridge!
[SCREAMS]

149
00:11:37,071 --> 00:11:40,366
Enemy units to port!
VF-10, what's wrong?

150
00:11:44,495 --> 00:11:47,081
- Missiles hit, no response.
- Enemy units, 12 o'clock!

151
00:11:47,248 --> 00:11:48,708
What the?! [SCREAMS]

152
00:11:52,336 --> 00:11:54,714
Enemy carrier-based craft
approaching, sir!

153
00:11:54,880 --> 00:11:58,676
- Admiral: Energy level? - Energy injection
will be complete in sixty seconds, sir.

154
00:11:59,176 --> 00:12:01,095
And what about our escort ships?

155
00:12:01,178 --> 00:12:03,498
They're all currently engaged
with enemy fighters, Admiral.

156
00:12:04,348 --> 00:12:06,392
Woodsman Unit, launching now!

157
00:12:06,892 --> 00:12:08,894
Woodsman Unit, launch complete!

158
00:12:09,103 --> 00:12:11,355
Enemy units closing fast!

159
00:12:11,939 --> 00:12:14,442
Woodsman to all units:
go to Circus Formation A.

160
00:12:14,608 --> 00:12:16,861
- Roger!
- Roger!

161
00:12:20,489 --> 00:12:22,867
Damn you! You're
not getting away!

162
00:12:25,828 --> 00:12:27,413
No!

163
00:12:28,873 --> 00:12:31,834
- Yellow, one's headed your way.
- What about the other one?

164
00:12:32,001 --> 00:12:34,712
He's headed for the bridge
of the FX. Red, cut him off!

165
00:12:36,172 --> 00:12:39,884
What the hell...?
What's happening?!

166
00:12:40,384 --> 00:12:43,220
We're not going to make it!
Oh my god, it's-!

167
00:12:43,804 --> 00:12:45,389
Enemy unit is punching through!

168
00:12:47,767 --> 00:12:50,770
[ALL GASP]

169
00:12:54,273 --> 00:12:57,526
That's amazing! That new
reflection shield really works!

170
00:12:57,693 --> 00:13:00,821
Energy injection to main guns
is now complete, sir.

171
00:13:00,988 --> 00:13:02,573
Good, start the countdown.

172
00:13:02,740 --> 00:13:05,326
Sir, main gun one's tracking
device is showing an error.

173
00:13:05,493 --> 00:13:08,162
Hmm... Can the computers
correct the error?

174
00:13:08,579 --> 00:13:11,707
Something's wrong in tracking.
I'm switching to manual.

175
00:13:11,791 --> 00:13:15,586
Targeting reticule centered.
Distance: two-zero, two-zero.

176
00:13:15,878 --> 00:13:18,464
Angle of fire, check!
Elevation, check!

177
00:13:19,173 --> 00:13:21,675
What the-?!
[SCREAMS]

178
00:13:23,761 --> 00:13:25,971
[BUILDING SUSPENSE MUSIC]

179
00:13:26,138 --> 00:13:28,516
Admiral, no response from
main guns one or two.

180
00:13:28,682 --> 00:13:31,602
Switch main fire control
to the secondary bridge!

181
00:13:32,186 --> 00:13:34,063
The secondary bridge
isn't responding either!

182
00:13:34,146 --> 00:13:36,357
[SCREAMS]

183
00:13:53,249 --> 00:13:55,292
No! We have no choice!

184
00:13:55,376 --> 00:13:57,378
[SCREAMS]

185
00:14:03,259 --> 00:14:08,681
[DISTANT ALARMS]

186
00:14:09,098 --> 00:14:14,645
[DISTANT EXPLOSIONS]

187
00:14:18,065 --> 00:14:20,067
[TRANQUIL TRILLS]

188
00:14:31,704 --> 00:14:33,706
[URBAN AMBIENCE]

189
00:14:45,175 --> 00:14:48,137
Yes, sir. Nothing to report.

190
00:14:48,220 --> 00:14:51,098
Right. We'll reinforce
the security at once.

191
00:14:52,057 --> 00:14:55,394
[YAWNS] These new orders
just make no sense.

192
00:14:55,561 --> 00:14:56,687
No sense, how?

193
00:14:56,854 --> 00:15:01,025
Well, you know, this place was attacked by
right-wing guerillas back when the war started...

194
00:15:01,108 --> 00:15:02,943
but we handled it.

195
00:15:03,110 --> 00:15:05,446
However, there's been nothing
for the last six months.

196
00:15:05,529 --> 00:15:07,406
And now they want to
double the security?

197
00:15:07,573 --> 00:15:11,243
Well, if we knew what the brass were
thinkin', we wouldn't be guards, right?

198
00:15:11,410 --> 00:15:13,871
I guess I just wish everything
would stay like it is now...

199
00:15:13,954 --> 00:15:16,194
and the war would end without
anything else happening.

200
00:15:35,643 --> 00:15:37,269
[PARTY SOUNDS]

201
00:15:39,939 --> 00:15:43,025
[LAUGHTER]

202
00:15:45,235 --> 00:15:48,113
[LAUGHS]

203
00:15:48,197 --> 00:15:53,410
And when I took his gun, that cop's face
looked like a blowfish caught in a net.

204
00:15:53,577 --> 00:15:56,455
Ah, yeah, makes you
feel good, don't it?

205
00:15:56,622 --> 00:16:02,836
[LAUGHS] Man, that is so far out! You shoulda
seen the way I just, like, elbowed...

206
00:16:03,003 --> 00:16:06,090
Glam: Damn, it's noisy. How'm I
supposed to concentrate in here?

207
00:16:06,256 --> 00:16:09,343
Dump: You always say that...
whenever you're losing.

208
00:16:09,510 --> 00:16:11,595
Oh, yeah?

209
00:16:11,762 --> 00:16:13,514
Always blaming others.

210
00:16:17,893 --> 00:16:19,520
I waited...

211
00:16:19,603 --> 00:16:22,648
but you never came back
for me. What happened?

212
00:16:22,815 --> 00:16:26,527
The reason I didn't go back to your place
is because I knew you'd be there.

213
00:16:26,610 --> 00:16:30,531
And what would have been the point of both
of us getting stuck in the mess I was in?

214
00:16:30,614 --> 00:16:33,117
I didn't want any
of this to happen.

215
00:16:33,200 --> 00:16:35,995
But at least I kept both of us
from becoming losers.

216
00:16:37,121 --> 00:16:39,915
I moved out. I waited for weeks...

217
00:16:39,999 --> 00:16:42,418
but I couldn't stand the looks.

218
00:16:42,501 --> 00:16:46,005
\"There she goes...
the lover of that murderer.\"

219
00:16:46,088 --> 00:16:50,342
And besides, how long could I keep waiting
for someone who might've been dead?

220
00:16:50,426 --> 00:16:53,637
[SIGHS] I'm not a strong
person, Shogo.

221
00:16:53,721 --> 00:16:55,764
I can't survive alone.

222
00:16:55,931 --> 00:17:00,477
- Yeah.
- Man, what's up with our two lovebirds?

223
00:17:01,687 --> 00:17:03,897
Hey, lighten up, you two.

224
00:17:03,981 --> 00:17:07,609
Six months! That's
how long it's been.

225
00:17:07,693 --> 00:17:11,071
After all that time, I know what
most of us would be doing now.

226
00:17:11,155 --> 00:17:13,949
And it ain't talking.

227
00:17:14,116 --> 00:17:16,577
You guys are smart.

228
00:17:16,660 --> 00:17:18,662
I guess you've all got stories.

229
00:17:18,829 --> 00:17:22,499
Not smart, tough. When you've been
rejected by the world, you have to be.

230
00:17:22,666 --> 00:17:24,585
Shogo's girlfriend is hot.

231
00:17:24,752 --> 00:17:27,171
Cyndi: Hey, he's got more
going on than you think.

232
00:17:27,337 --> 00:17:32,468
Reina: Shogo may still look like a little kid,
