00:35:43,391 --> 00:35:44,976
What about these branches here?

460
00:35:45,143 --> 00:35:48,855
We have it covered, sir. This path
leads to the south corridor...

461
00:35:48,938 --> 00:35:52,608
while this one merges with it, and
also leads to the south corridor.

462
00:35:52,692 --> 00:35:55,486
The narrow one's a dead end,
and at the far end we have...

463
00:35:55,570 --> 00:35:59,991
- three Flaggers and two full squads waiting.
They won't escape. - Where are they now?

464
00:36:00,158 --> 00:36:03,369
B Squad and the Sergeant are driving
them from two different directions.

465
00:36:03,452 --> 00:36:05,746
They're heading straight
into our trap.

466
00:36:35,026 --> 00:36:37,278
Looks like they're gone.

467
00:36:37,904 --> 00:36:39,906
[MECHANICAL CLANKING]

468
00:36:43,367 --> 00:36:46,329
Hmm...? [GRUNTS]
It's morning.

469
00:36:46,495 --> 00:36:50,374
[YAWNS] And the trains'll
start running soon.

470
00:36:50,541 --> 00:36:52,752
Hey... what's this thing?

471
00:36:53,628 --> 00:36:56,464
Hmm... a transmitter, I think.

472
00:36:56,631 --> 00:36:58,549
Hey, let me see that.

473
00:36:58,716 --> 00:37:00,676
[TRAIN APPROACHING]

474
00:37:03,387 --> 00:37:06,224
[SNICKERS]

475
00:37:10,436 --> 00:37:12,563
[LAUGHTER]

476
00:37:13,981 --> 00:37:15,781
- [RAPID BEEPS]
- There's no escape this time.

477
00:37:15,942 --> 00:37:18,319
Have you located the
transmitters yet?

478
00:37:19,528 --> 00:37:23,157
They've been separated, sir. One's in
Shinjuku, and the other's in Minato.

479
00:37:23,783 --> 00:37:26,661
So they've found the decoy,
as expected. Good.

480
00:37:26,744 --> 00:37:30,122
We're returning to HQ.
Keep us updated.

481
00:37:31,040 --> 00:37:33,459
So, where did they hide the
second transmitter?

482
00:37:33,626 --> 00:37:35,419
Inside the mirror.

483
00:37:35,586 --> 00:37:38,065
- You are the Eve I spoke to before, right?
- [MYSTERIOUS MUSIC]

484
00:37:38,089 --> 00:37:40,174
- The real Eve?
- Yes.

485
00:37:40,341 --> 00:37:43,719
But this program has been purged from
the majority of Bahamut's memory...

486
00:37:43,803 --> 00:37:46,555
and can no longer access
the external work systems.

487
00:37:46,764 --> 00:37:51,727
However, I believe that if my external connections
to the main system were to be severed...

488
00:37:51,811 --> 00:37:54,814
I would then be able to function
as an independent system.

489
00:37:54,981 --> 00:37:58,818
Hold on. Exactly where would
this main system be located?

490
00:37:58,985 --> 00:38:03,948
On Bahamut's Seventh Level, Area 49BA,
as shown in this display.

491
00:38:04,490 --> 00:38:06,617
So it's inside Bahamut.

492
00:38:06,784 --> 00:38:10,288
That is correct. However,
there is little time left.

493
00:38:10,371 --> 00:38:12,832
You must come to me as
quickly as possible.

494
00:38:12,999 --> 00:38:15,084
If what she says is true...

495
00:38:15,167 --> 00:38:18,796
then we could bust our way into
Bahamut and set Eve free, right?

496
00:38:19,297 --> 00:38:21,757
Please come as quickly
as possible.

497
00:38:21,841 --> 00:38:24,260
There are things that I
must do that I cannot.

498
00:38:24,760 --> 00:38:26,554
But what can I do?

499
00:38:26,721 --> 00:38:29,140
Quite a lot, if you
bring friends, right?

500
00:38:29,307 --> 00:38:31,600
- Are you with me?!
- [GENERAL AGREEMENT]

501
00:38:31,767 --> 00:38:34,061
We're with you, Shogo!

502
00:38:34,228 --> 00:38:38,065
[CONTINUED CHEERING]

503
00:38:38,232 --> 00:38:40,276
Yeah!

504
00:38:40,443 --> 00:38:42,820
Then it's decided.
Let's do it!

505
00:38:50,619 --> 00:38:51,619
What do we have?

506
00:38:51,704 --> 00:38:54,874
We located transmitter one
attached to a train to otemachi.

507
00:38:54,957 --> 00:38:57,043
However, transmitter two
is in Roppongi.

508
00:38:57,126 --> 00:38:59,126
For the last thirty minutes
it's been stationary...

509
00:38:59,170 --> 00:39:02,340
nine meters underground, at the
site of an old embassy building.

510
00:39:04,216 --> 00:39:06,344
Damn! They're right
under our noses...

511
00:39:06,510 --> 00:39:09,221
- [PHONE RINGING]
- [DRAMATIC TAPS]

512
00:39:09,388 --> 00:39:13,017
Front gate. Huh? Yes sir!
Acknowledged!

513
00:39:17,688 --> 00:39:20,358
Man! We're gonna meet Eve!

514
00:39:20,441 --> 00:39:25,279
Screw the cops! Screw the army!
I'm really gonna meet her!

515
00:39:25,446 --> 00:39:29,575
Oooh... So, are you taking
a notepad for signing?

516
00:39:29,742 --> 00:39:34,038
Yeah. And I'm gonna get her picture,
and shake her hand. [LAUGHS]

517
00:39:34,205 --> 00:39:37,208
Asshole, there ain't no way
she's shaking your hand!

518
00:39:37,375 --> 00:39:39,293
Shut up!

519
00:39:39,502 --> 00:39:41,462
[ALARM BUZZER]

520
00:39:43,214 --> 00:39:47,343
Remember: Don't let them know you're out
there until they're completely surrounded.

521
00:39:49,303 --> 00:39:50,888
- Keep it moving! Hurry!
- Yes, sir!

522
00:39:51,680 --> 00:39:53,516
[EXCITED CONVERSATION]

523
00:39:53,682 --> 00:39:55,851
Hey Jayce, toss me
some of that, will'ya?

524
00:39:59,605 --> 00:40:01,065
Bleeeaah!

525
00:40:01,232 --> 00:40:03,776
- Bam-bam-bam-bam-bam!
- [LAUGHS]

526
00:40:04,110 --> 00:40:06,028
[DRAMATIC BEATS]

527
00:40:08,447 --> 00:40:12,952
The 3rd and 4th Companies? Those are from
the Nakano Division. Yes, understood.

528
00:40:13,119 --> 00:40:16,080
- Move it, people! Move it!
- Almost there, sir!

529
00:40:19,333 --> 00:40:20,626
Come on!

530
00:40:32,430 --> 00:40:35,599
[EXCITED CHATTER]

531
00:40:38,686 --> 00:40:41,772
Lightning! Trouble!
Big trouble!

532
00:40:41,856 --> 00:40:44,942
Cops everywhere! We're
completely surrounded!

533
00:40:46,152 --> 00:40:47,695
[WAR CRIES]

534
00:40:47,987 --> 00:40:51,240
Hey! Take the back way,
and I'll cover ya!

535
00:40:51,323 --> 00:40:54,285
Gene, Suri-ko, Ike! Follow me!

536
00:40:57,037 --> 00:41:00,916
Use the secret exit while Guts' team
holds the front! Evacuate!

537
00:41:01,000 --> 00:41:04,628
- Jayce, you and your squad head for Shibuya.
- Riot! - You got it!

538
00:41:04,795 --> 00:41:06,755
- Watch you ass!
- OK.

539
00:41:06,922 --> 00:41:11,510
Cyndi, Yui can't handle a bike and a weapon
at the same time, so cover her rear!

540
00:41:11,969 --> 00:41:16,390
- It's covered! - Thanks.
- Yui, make sure you stay close to me!

541
00:41:16,765 --> 00:41:20,144
And you stick by me, Shogo,
even if you're dead!

542
00:41:20,311 --> 00:41:23,606
Just remember, that
works both ways!

543
00:41:26,400 --> 00:41:29,528
- We're in, sir. - [ANNUNCIATOR]
- Huh...

544
00:41:30,654 --> 00:41:33,532
Transmitter two's moving.
It's heading southwest, sir.

545
00:41:34,783 --> 00:41:37,036
- Send the Garlands in now.
- Yes, sir.

546
00:41:37,203 --> 00:41:38,829
Gaaaah!

547
00:41:39,371 --> 00:41:42,666
I'm Guts, Suicide King!
Who wants to dance?

548
00:41:42,833 --> 00:41:45,002
- Take him down!
- Yeah!

549
00:41:53,052 --> 00:41:54,345
Eat this!

550
00:42:01,560 --> 00:42:03,938
Go to hell, you pigs!

551
00:42:06,649 --> 00:42:08,651
That's it! Go!

552
00:42:13,072 --> 00:42:15,115
Aw, shit!

553
00:42:18,744 --> 00:42:20,746
That's it! To hell with you!

554
00:42:26,043 --> 00:42:27,878
Kick his metal ass!

555
00:42:33,217 --> 00:42:35,654
We've lost track of transmitter two,
sir, and our containment of...

556
00:42:35,678 --> 00:42:38,055
blocks B37 and A40
has been breached.

557
00:42:38,138 --> 00:42:40,538
I'm afraid most of them managed
to make it out into the city.

558
00:42:40,683 --> 00:42:44,562
Get a helicopter up on the roof.
I'll be handling this part personally.

559
00:42:44,645 --> 00:42:47,481
- How long will it take?
- I'll have it there in five minutes, sir.

560
00:42:47,648 --> 00:42:49,149
Understood.

561
00:42:51,485 --> 00:42:55,114
Oooh! So scary!

562
00:42:55,406 --> 00:42:59,618
I don't care how many there are,
you're not getting past me! [LAUGHS]

563
00:42:59,785 --> 00:43:00,911
Fire!

564
00:43:01,412 --> 00:43:03,497
[LAUGHS]

565
00:43:05,124 --> 00:43:07,126
[CHUCKLES]

566
00:43:09,753 --> 00:43:11,046
[SOMBER ROCK BEAT]

567
00:43:12,423 --> 00:43:14,258
\"Honored Parents...\"

568
00:43:14,341 --> 00:43:18,262
\"I am sorry I have not
contacted you recently.\"

569
00:43:18,345 --> 00:43:22,433
\"I cannot divulge why;
however, at this moment...\"

570
00:43:22,516 --> 00:43:26,687
\"I am on a mission I must complete,
even if the cost is my own life.\"

571
00:43:28,022 --> 00:43:32,860
\"If you are reading this letter, I will
no longer be a part of this world.\"

572
00:43:33,360 --> 00:43:37,448
\"I know that this is not something that
a son should do to his parents, but...\"

573
00:43:37,531 --> 00:43:40,200
\"I feel great honor
in my work.\"

574
00:43:40,284 --> 00:43:43,704
\"Please forgive me for being
such an inconsiderate son...\"

575
00:43:43,787 --> 00:43:46,707
\"and forgive me for
leaving this world first.\"

576
00:43:46,790 --> 00:43:49,835
\"I hope for your good health,
and please take care.\"

577
00:43:49,918 --> 00:43:52,880
\"- Yuichiro Shiratori.\"

578
00:43:53,047 --> 00:43:55,424
[DRAMATIC ACTION ROCK MUSIC]

579
00:44:17,154 --> 00:44:18,739
Yeah! C'mon!

580
00:44:19,615 --> 00:44:21,700
Dudes, this is one
helluva field trip!

581
00:44:26,664 --> 00:44:29,833
OK, I'm tired of running!
It's your turn!

582
00:44:30,000 --> 00:44:31,168
[SHOCK]

583
00:44:34,129 --> 00:44:36,674
Man, that was just sad!
[LAUGHS]

584
00:44:41,720 --> 00:44:44,682
Can't you read? This road's
closed to through traffic.

585
00:44:45,015 --> 00:44:49,353
How can those kids beat you? Use the
Flaggers to drive them into the open.

586
00:44:49,436 --> 00:44:51,855
You heard me!
Playtime is over!

587
00:44:51,939 --> 00:44:54,650
And where's Yahagi?
Haven't you located him yet?

588
00:44:54,858 --> 00:44:58,278
- [EXCITED WHOOPS]
- Reinforce the entrance to the second level!

589
00:44:58,445 --> 00:45:01,156
All right! Here they come!

590
00:45:08,414 --> 00:45:10,249
Here!

591
00:45:11,125 --> 00:45:13,669
[EXCITED YELLS]

592
00:45:21,468 --> 00:45:23,971
Yo! Lets have some fun!

593
00:45:27,307 --> 00:45:30,686
Those are just decoys!
Move in and eliminate them!

594
00:45:39,611 --> 00:45:41,613
Huh?! What the hell?!

595
00:45:42,322 --> 00:45:44,241
That little bastard!

596
00:45:46,243 --> 00:45:48,245
Eyaah!

597
00:45:52,207 --> 00:45:54,877
Woah! That was radical!

598
00:45:57,379 --> 00:45:58,505
Eat this!

599
00:46:15,105 --> 00:46:17,232
Fire!

600
00:46:28,911 --> 00:46:31,455
[GROANS]

601
00:46:31,622 --> 00:46:35,000
What's the matter?
Want some more?

602
00:46:35,083 --> 00:46:36,752
[GRUNTS]

603
00:46:36,835 --> 00:46:39,379
Where's Yahagi hiding?

604
00:46:39,546 --> 00:46:44,760
How the fuck should I know? If you want him
so bad, find him your own fucking self!

605
00:46:47,387 --> 00:46:49,431
You got a big mouth, bitch!

606
00:46:55,854 --> 00:46:58,524
We've spotted a group traveling
east near Aoyama Avenue.

607
00:46:58,607 --> 00:47:02,027
We believe it includes the
Proto-Garland and Shogo Yahagi.

608
00:47:02,444 --> 00:47:04,988
Right. Converge the Flaggers
on that point!

609
00:47:24,174 --> 00:47:28,053
- [ALERT SIRENS] - Enemy infiltration
on the second floor, Block 29!

610
00:47:28,220 --> 00:47:30,347
The 5th Ground Unit is responding.

611
00:47:31,056 --> 00:47:36,562
Send Centurion Unit Number 3 to Block 29.
I want that situation handled.

612
00:47:37,229 --> 00:47:39,439
What's Shiratori's current status?

613
00:47:39,606 --> 00:47:43,527
The Lieutenant reports they're about to
corner the Proto-Garland and Yahagi, sir.

614
00:47:43,694 --> 00:47:45,612
Tell them to hurry!

615
00:47:45,821 --> 00:47:47,739
[ENERGETIC ROCK MUSIC]

616
00:47:54,329 --> 00:47:56,415
Yui! You OK back there?

617
00:47:56,582 --> 00:47:58,917
Sure! Don't forget,
she's got me!

618
00:47:59,084 --> 00:48:00,460
Keep it up!

619
00:48:00,627 --> 00:48:02,921
Back off!

620
00:48:03,005 --> 00:48:06,300
Out of bullets!
[SCREAMS]

621
00:48:10,721 --> 00:48:12,472
Cyndi, rear-view!

622
00:48:12,556 --> 00:48:15,642
Motherfucker!

623
00:48:21,398 --> 00:48:24,234
I think it's time for the Trash
to hit the tracks!

624
00:48:32,326 --> 00:48:36,330
They're trying to enter
Bahamut via Shaft 16.

625
00:48:36,413 --> 00:48:41,043
All units, proceed to D-4.
We've got to cut them off!

626
00:48:49,301 --> 00:48:50,761
Leave this to me.

627
00:48:50,844 --> 00:48:53,722
Get off our fucking asses,
you bastards!

628
00:49:03,273 --> 00:49:06,193
They're just ahead of us!
Turn around! [SCREAMS]

629
00:49:14,701 --> 00:49:17,079
Time to hit full throttle!

630
00:49:26,713 --> 00:49:28,507
That was too close!

631
00:49:31,969 --> 00:49:33,804
Huh?

632
00:49:35,973 --> 00:49:38,100
[MUSIC RESOLVES]

633
00:49:38,266 --> 00:49:40,394
End of the line, Yahagi!

634
00:49:40,477 --> 00:49:45,399
If you don't want to lose any more of
your friends, you'll surrender quietly.

635
00:49:45,482 --> 00:49:49,820
As for the rest of you, get off your bikes
and raise your hands in the air.

636
00:49:50,153 --> 00:49:53,240
No way! We can't stop
after coming this far!

637
00:49:53,407 --> 00:49:56,201
- Just leave this to me.
- Shogo!

638
00:49:56,368 --> 00:49:58,954
I'm warning you. Try anything,
and we'll shoot!

639
00:49:59,287 --> 00:50:02,582
- All right, I'm coming.
- No, Shogo. Wait!

640
00:50:02,749 --> 00:50:05,836
- You're better than that, Shogo!
- Don't be a chickenshit!

641
00:50:06,003 --> 00:50:07,921
Drive forward slowly.

642
00:50:11,091 --> 00:50:13,635
That's far enough!
Drop your weapon!

643
00:50:14,636 --> 00:50:18,598
Now raise your hands slowly, stand up,
and get off the Garland.

644
00:50:19,474 --> 00:50:23,562
Hold it! Show me what's in
your hands! Show me!

645
00:50:24,688 --> 00:50:27,649
- Ha! Suckers!
- [EXCITING MUSIC]

646
00:50:29,735 --> 00:50:31,987
- Awesome!
- Right! Let's go!

647
00:50:36,324 --> 00:50:38,452
- Don't worry, it's me.
- Shogo!

648
00:50:38,618 --> 00:50:40,245
C'mon! This way!

649
00:50:40,412 --> 00:50:44,416
We're dead without out bikes.
But I've got an idea.

650
00:50:45,000 --> 00:50:48,378
They must be hiding here someplace!
We can't let them escape!

651
00:50:51,882 --> 00:50:54,217
Incoming!

652
00:51:00,057 --> 00:51:03,977
Get ready to take him out!
Wait, that's not a Garland!

653
00:51:04,144 --> 00:51:07,314
- Eyaaah!
- Eyuuuh!

654
00:51:07,481 --> 00:51:09,667
We missed the first two, but they
were on standard bikes.

655
00:51:09,691 --> 00:51:12,235
Forget the small fry!
Catch the Proto-Garland!

656
00:51:12,402 --> 00:51:14,571
Are you OK, Glam?

657
00:51:14,654 --> 00:51:17,949
Looks like we're both going
to be screwed this time.

658
00:51:18,116 --> 00:51:24,039
[GASP] It figures. It's like those
big-budget action flicks. [GROANS]

659
00:51:24,122 --> 00:51:27,292
The secondary characters
always get killed off.

660
00:51:27,375 --> 00:51:30,504
But if I'm going, it's going
to be with some class.

661
00:51:30,670 --> 00:51:35,550
Geez! Only you would be concerned about
dying in some really pretentious fashion.

662
00:51:35,634 --> 00:51:37,636
[GRUNTS]

663
00:51:38,512 --> 00:51:44,184
Shogo, run! We'll handle our own
screwups. We're not kids!

664
00:51:44,351 --> 00:51:46,645
- That's right!
- Come on out, Yahagi!

665
00:51:46,728 --> 00:51:48,563
Or your friends are going
to burn to death!

666
00:51:52,442 --> 00:51:55,237
Shogo! No! Why didn't you run?

667
00:51:55,403 --> 00:51:57,531
Leave us, you idiot!

668
00:51:59,282 --> 00:52:01,284
[MUSIC RESOLVES]

669
00:52:02,869 --> 00:52:05,455
You're nothing but kids!
A bunch of damn brats!

670
00:52:05,539 --> 00:52:08,375
How dare you mock the military!
How dare you?!

671
00:52:12,963 --> 00:52:15,257
[GASPS, GRUNTS]

672
00:52:18,051 --> 00:52:21,221
So, you're out of ammunition,
are you?

673
00:52:21,304 --> 00:52:23,807
Come on out of there, Yahagi!

674
00:52:32,107 --> 00:52:34,276
[CHUCKLES]

675
00:52:34,359 --> 00:52:37,696
[LAUGHS UPROARIOUSLY]

676
00:52:40,448 --> 00:52:42,993
Sneaky little bastard!

677
00:52:43,160 --> 00:52:45,162
Bastard? Huh!

678
00:52:45,245 --> 00:52:49,958
Yahagi? So sorry!

679
00:52:50,041 --> 00:52:54,754
Wrong asshole!
[LAUGHS DEMENTEDLY]

680
00:52:54,921 --> 00:52:58,717
- Hah! Wrong jackass in the box!
- [LAUGHTER]

681
00:52:58,800 --> 00:53:01,261
Help! We're under attack!

682
00:53:01,428 --> 00:53:04,055
No! It's impossible!
Not here!

683
00:53:07,142 --> 00:53:09,477
Commander! They've got
us surrounded!

684
00:53:09,644 --> 00:53:11,438
Shields! Use your sabres!

685
00:53:14,482 --> 00:53:16,193
What in the-?

686
00:53:16,359 --> 00:53:19,070
How could the enemy have
penetrated this far?

687
00:53:19,154 --> 00:53:22,324
Sergeant! Are you all right? The
brats pulled a fast one on us!

688
00:53:22,407 --> 00:53:24,910
Yahagi was the one
that escaped first!

689
00:53:25,243 --> 00:53:27,621
Sergeant! What's wrong,
Sergeant?!

690
00:53:31,875 --> 00:53:34,002
We made it!

691
00:53:34,169 --> 00:53:37,923
That came from back where
Lightning was! You don't think...?

692
00:53:38,757 --> 00:53:41,426
No way! He's immortal.

693
00:53:41,593 --> 00:53:43,178
[MYSTERIOUS MUSIC]

694
00:53:43,261 --> 00:53:45,347
Huh? Yui! Are you...?

695
00:53:45,513 --> 00:53:48,266
I... I'll be fine.

696
00:53:48,433 --> 00:53:50,227
We're almost there.

697
00:54:01,738 --> 00:54:03,323
Are you all right, Yui?

698
00:54:03,490 --> 00:54:05,784
Yeah...

699
00:54:08,036 --> 00:54:12,624
I'll wait here for Lightning
and the others. Be careful.

700
00:54:23,760 --> 00:54:26,179
We made it, Eve!
What should I do now?

701
00:54:26,972 --> 00:54:29,140
Operator... 7G?

702
00:54:29,307 --> 00:54:30,517
That's right.

703
00:54:30,684 --> 00:54:34,938
Confirming identification.
Please wait.

704
00:54:35,021 --> 00:54:39,109
Confirmed. I am now
removing the barrier seal.

705
00:54:39,276 --> 00:54:41,236
[MACHINES SPIN UP]

706
00:55:01,089 --> 00:55:04,384
Shogo, when you didn't
come back for me...

707
00:55:04,551 --> 00:55:06,803
Shhh... Don't try to speak.

708
00:55:08,596 --> 00:55:10,390
- [GROAN]
- [GASP]

709
00:55:10,557 --> 00:55:12,142
[SAD RISING NOTES]

710
00:55:12,309 --> 00:55:14,811
Hey Yui! Yui...!

711
00:55:16,563 --> 00:55:18,398
We've gotta get you to a doctor.

712
00:55:18,565 --> 00:55:22,610
No, Shogo! Please... I have
to ask you something first.

713
00:55:22,777 --> 00:55:24,529
But... you need help.

714
00:55:24,696 --> 00:55:26,698
Six months ago...

715
00:55:26,781 --> 00:55:29,242
I kept waiting for you...

716
00:55:29,326 --> 00:55:32,037
I kept waiting all night long.

717
00:55:32,454 --> 00:55:33,872
[SOFT GASP]

718
00:55:34,039 --> 00:55:38,251
And all the next month...
I kept waiting.

719
00:55:40,045 --> 00:55:41,963
Yui...

720
00:55:43,423 --> 00:55:45,633
Why didn't you come
back for me, Shogo?

721
00:55:45,800 --> 00:55:49,137
Because... I was trying
to protect you.

722
00:55:49,220 --> 00:55:52,390
- Because...
- What good is safe...?

723
00:55:54,601 --> 00:55:58,063
If I... couldn't be with you?

724
00:55:58,146 --> 00:55:59,814
[GASPS]

725
00:55:59,981 --> 00:56:02,984
Yui, hold on!
You can't die!

726
00:56:05,362 --> 00:56:07,864
- [EERIE MUSIC]
- Do not despair.

727
00:56:07,947 --> 00:56:10,867
Her life has not yet ended.

728
00:56:11,034 --> 00:56:12,452
Eve...

729
00:56:12,619 --> 00:56:15,622
Please, bring her here.

730
00:56:17,582 --> 00:56:19,667
You can help her?

731
00:56:29,636 --> 00:56:32,931
Hold on, Yui.
You can't die now.

732
00:56:33,098 --> 00:56:37,102
She will not. Treatment
is still possible.

733
00:56:41,981 --> 00:56:45,610
[GASPS] Eve?
Is something wrong?

734
00:56:50,615 --> 00:56:53,785
Please come over here and have
a seat, OK? Talk with me.

735
00:56:57,038 --> 00:56:59,582
I did come to you!

736
00:56:59,666 --> 00:57:01,876
And all of us risked our lives!

737
00:57:06,423 --> 00:57:10,176
And I didn't come all this way
just to watch you put on a show!

738
00:57:10,343 --> 00:57:14,305
Do not be upset.
But we need to talk.

739
00:57:14,931 --> 00:57:16,558
Then start talking, OK?

740
00:57:16,641 --> 00:57:19,644
Stop beating around the bush,
and be straight with me!

741
00:57:23,857 --> 00:57:27,152
Is this... all some kind of test?

742
00:57:29,904 --> 00:57:32,907
But what would you
be testing me for?

743
00:57:33,825 --> 00:57:36,202
I don't have anything to hide.

744
00:57:36,661 --> 00:57:38,413
Why didn't you join the army?

745
00:57:38,580 --> 00:57:42,041
I... I don't like the way
they do things.

746
00:57:42,208 --> 00:57:43,251
What don't you like?

747
00:57:43,418 --> 00:57:47,297
Let's start with the whole \"might makes
right\" mindset, and enforced conformity.

748
00:57:47,380 --> 00:57:49,799
And how if you're against
them, you're trashed.

749
00:57:49,883 --> 00:57:53,303
And how everything is handled
by procedure instead of thought.

750
00:57:56,598 --> 00:58:01,186
Five hundred years ago, mankind brought
Earth to the brink of total destruction.

751
00:58:01,269 --> 00:58:05,064
At that point, the United Nations passed
the Earth Preservation Law...

752
00:58:05,148 --> 00:58:07,400
and gave all control to ADAM.

753
00:58:07,484 --> 00:58:09,986
To allow the Earth time
to heal itself...

754
00:58:10,069 --> 00:58:14,866
the surviving cities were sent into
space for a period of five hundred years.

755
00:58:14,949 --> 00:58:16,910
Now that time has arrived.

756
00:58:18,203 --> 00:58:20,914
Tell me... do you love Yui?

757
00:58:21,080 --> 00:58:23,082
I like her.

758
00:58:23,249 --> 00:58:25,251
[WEIRD TRILL]

759
00:58:26,544 --> 00:58:28,630
Define \"like.\"

760
00:58:30,256 --> 00:58:33,343
It's how I feel like I always
want to be with her.

761
00:58:33,426 --> 00:58:35,929
How I want to protect
her from harm.

762
00:58:36,804 --> 00:58:41,142
[SIGHS] To be honest, if that's what
you want to define as love...

763
00:58:41,226 --> 00:58:43,561
I guess I love Yui.

764
00:58:44,103 --> 00:58:49,275
Or, more accurately,
that I'm beginning to.

765
00:58:49,442 --> 00:58:52,904
If you had a wish,
what would it be?

766
00:58:53,071 --> 00:58:54,614
[SIGHS]

767
00:58:54,697 --> 00:58:57,325
That I could go back
to my favorite cafe...

768
00:58:57,408 --> 00:58:59,410
My friend's bike shop...

769
00:58:59,494 --> 00:59:03,248
Hang out with my friends, and ride our
bikes through the old neighborhood, y'know?

770
00:59:03,414 --> 00:59:07,168
- Uh-huh.
- To be able to see 'em whenever I want.

771
00:59:07,252 --> 00:59:10,380
Or just to talk on the phone,
and shoot the bull.

772
00:59:10,463 --> 00:59:15,468
I want to live... and be happy.
That's all, really.

773
00:59:18,930 --> 00:59:22,350
What does... being an adult
mean to you, Shogo?

774
00:59:22,517 --> 00:59:25,019
[SIGHS] An adult...

775
00:59:25,103 --> 00:59:27,939
Well, it's something I wanted
to be when I was little.

776
00:59:28,356 --> 00:59:31,276
But now I've learned to see
adults for what they really are.

777
00:59:31,359 --> 00:59:34,862
Lying, hurting, killing each
other, and for what?!

778
00:59:34,946 --> 00:59:38,866
To make themselves rich.
To gain more power!

779
00:59:38,950 --> 00:59:41,536
They do it just
because they can!

780
00:59:41,619 --> 00:59:44,831
That's why! And that's why
I don't want to be an adult!

781
00:59:44,914 --> 00:59:49,127
Not if it means being like them, and
not the ones I worshipped as a kid!

782
00:59:49,210 --> 00:59:52,630
The ones I saw in the
movies, and on TV.

783
00:59:55,216 --> 01:00:00,138
[SIGHS] Could you do that? Be like
the adults you admired back then?

784
01:00:00,305 --> 01:00:03,391
You mean, be...
an adult?

785
01:00:03,558 --> 01:00:08,021
If you could, you could change
this whole misguided society.

786
01:00:08,104 --> 01:00:09,856
- Will you?
- Now, hold on, Eve-

787
01:00:10,023 --> 01:00:10,857
[SYNTHESIZED QUAVER]

788
01:00:11,024 --> 01:00:13,443
Why are you asking
me these things?

789
01:00:13,610 --> 01:00:15,320
[PULSING ALERT]

790
01:00:15,486 --> 01:00:17,530
[SOFT GASP]

791
01:00:24,495 --> 01:00:27,874
ADAM is calling me.
I must answer.

792
01:00:28,041 --> 01:00:31,669
- What the? - What happened?
- What's going on? - What happened?

793
01:00:32,378 --> 01:00:34,130
[BASS RUMBLE]

794
01:00:38,343 --> 01:00:41,387
Where's this data coming
from? Analyze it!

795
01:00:41,554 --> 01:00:45,183
- It's something called ADAM!
- We can't block it, or convert it.

796
01:00:45,350 --> 01:00:49,562
The ADAM protocols are
loading... Initiated.

797
01:00:49,729 --> 01:00:52,690
But as for mankind's
return to Earth...

798
01:00:52,774 --> 01:00:56,069
only the ADAM program can
make that determination...

799
01:00:56,152 --> 01:00:59,864
as to whether the data I send
meets the allowed criteria.

800
01:01:00,365 --> 01:01:03,576
The EVE program was designed
to return to Earth...

801
01:01:03,660 --> 01:01:07,330
only those who would not
repeat the same mistakes.

802
01:01:07,413 --> 01:01:10,083
I am now sending
my data to ADAM.

803
01:01:13,795 --> 01:01:16,172
You said the Earth. Is that
where we're heading?

804
01:01:16,339 --> 01:01:19,217
We are already there.
However...

805
01:01:19,384 --> 01:01:23,221
- What? - Is this for real?
- The Earth? She can't be serious!

806
01:01:23,388 --> 01:01:26,557
Won't this ADAM let us
return to Earth?

807
01:01:28,393 --> 01:01:30,478
I'm afraid I don't know.

808
01:01:30,645 --> 01:01:32,063
But why not?

809
01:01:32,230 --> 01:01:36,275
Because ADAM is refusing
to answer my queries.

810
01:01:36,359 --> 01:01:40,154
His authority supersedes my own.
I cannot make him answer.

811
01:01:40,321 --> 01:01:42,323
[CONTEMPLATIVE MUSIC]

812
01:01:46,994 --> 01:01:49,455
Hey, it's OK.

813
01:01:49,539 --> 01:01:53,918
Actually, I'm not sure we're good enough
to warrant continuing anyway.

814
01:01:55,420 --> 01:01:59,465
I'm just glad that someone cares
about me and my friends.

815
01:02:00,883 --> 01:02:04,095
And that I could meet you.
Thank you, Eve.

816
01:02:06,848 --> 01:02:08,641
Thank you...

817
01:02:10,351 --> 01:02:12,353
Thank you, Shogo.

818
01:02:15,732 --> 01:02:18,943
Please don't let go of the
hope in your hearts.

819
01:02:19,026 --> 01:02:22,572
I will do everything
I can for you.

820
01:02:22,655 --> 01:02:24,031
For all of you.

821
01:02:25,575 --> 01:02:27,618
I won't.

822
01:02:27,785 --> 01:02:29,787
[PHASE OUT]

823
01:03:03,863 --> 01:03:05,990
Shogo? Where's Yui?

824
01:03:06,157 --> 01:03:07,742
With Eve.

825
01:03:07,825 --> 01:03:10,119
So where are Lightning and
the rest of the gang?

826
01:03:10,286 --> 01:03:12,538
They haven't made it yet.

827
01:03:13,289 --> 01:03:15,625
- You don't think they-
- They'll be here.

828
01:03:15,708 --> 01:03:17,418
Lightning's immortal, remember?

829
01:03:17,502 --> 01:03:20,713
- [VEHICLE APPROACHING] - Huh...?
- [GASP] - Someone's coming!

830
01:03:20,880 --> 01:03:22,256
[MECHA TWANG]

831
01:03:22,423 --> 01:03:24,091
Yahagi!

832
01:03:24,175 --> 01:03:25,051
[GASPS]

833
01:03:25,134 --> 01:03:28,888
You're... not getting away,
you bastard!

834
01:03:28,971 --> 01:03:30,181
[GROANS]

835
01:03:41,609 --> 01:03:43,152
- He's dead.
- [METALLIC CLANK]

836
01:03:43,319 --> 01:03:45,488
[GASPS] Shogo!

837
01:03:47,156 --> 01:03:50,785
Oh my god, the sonofabitch
really is immortal!

838
01:03:50,952 --> 01:03:52,245
You really are alive!

839
01:03:52,411 --> 01:03:54,497
Don't kill me off just yet!

840
01:03:56,874 --> 01:03:58,751
- You bastard!
- You had us worried.

841
01:03:58,918 --> 01:04:01,295
You scared the piss out of me!

842
01:04:01,462 --> 01:04:03,464
- [SNIFFLES]
- Sorry we're late.

843
01:04:03,548 --> 01:04:06,843
[SIGHS] Dump was dragging
her ass. [LAUGHS]

844
01:04:07,009 --> 01:04:08,928
Well, excuse me!

845
01:04:09,095 --> 01:04:12,431
Glam's just out cold.
So where's Yui got to?

846
01:04:12,598 --> 01:04:17,061
- I left her with Eve.
- So you met her? Really?

847
01:04:17,228 --> 01:04:18,938
Yeah...

848
01:04:19,105 --> 01:04:21,107
- That's awesome!
- Yeah...

849
01:04:21,274 --> 01:04:23,276
Thanks to you guys.

850
01:04:40,501 --> 01:04:44,505
Sir, Bahamut has now completely removed
itself from our control system.

851
01:04:46,632 --> 01:04:49,969
The entire Megazone
is starting to fall apart.

852
01:04:52,054 --> 01:04:55,558
The ADAM program is now
controlling everything, sir.

853
01:04:56,309 --> 01:05:00,271
It's ordering Megazone 23
to tear itself to pieces.

854
01:05:10,489 --> 01:05:14,702
Sixty minutes until complete collapse.
And there's more, sir.

855
01:05:14,869 --> 01:05:18,789
We've been detected by defense
systems on the Moon?

856
01:05:24,420 --> 01:05:26,422
[DRAMATIC MUSIC]

857
01:05:42,188 --> 01:05:44,982
All forces, cancel
current operations.

858
01:05:45,066 --> 01:05:51,030
All units will escort as many residents as possible
to either the spaceport or emergency shelters...

859
01:05:51,113 --> 01:05:54,033
after which, we will
abandon MZ23.

860
01:05:54,116 --> 01:05:57,370
Citizens of Tokyo, this is
a national emergency.

861
01:05:57,453 --> 01:06:02,124
Please remain calm, and proceed to the nearest
public shelter as quickly as possible.

862
01:06:02,291 --> 01:06:05,836
You are to take whatever spaceships
are left on Megazone 23...

863
01:06:05,920 --> 01:06:09,715
and get as many of the citizens off
as possible. Is that understood?

864
01:06:09,882 --> 01:06:11,842
All: Yes, sir!

865
01:06:12,301 --> 01:06:14,303
[FAINT CONFUSED CROWD CHATTER]

866
01:06:16,973 --> 01:06:20,518
Shuttles from this shelter are proceeding
towards the spaceport.

867
01:06:20,601 --> 01:06:25,982
There's no danger! Please remain calm and
move quickly to the rear of the shelter!

868
01:06:40,621 --> 01:06:43,541
I see. So that's how it is.

869
01:06:43,624 --> 01:06:46,460
I'm in love with Eve
all over again.

870
01:06:46,627 --> 01:06:50,006
- You and me both.
- Hey hey! You've already got Yui, you dog!

871
01:06:50,172 --> 01:06:52,425
And you've got me!
I want a ring!

872
01:06:52,591 --> 01:06:54,301
Ow! OK, OK, you got it!

873
01:06:54,468 --> 01:06:58,347
- How are you guys?
- Well, my head's swollen... bigtime.

874
01:06:58,764 --> 01:07:01,684
But, that's normal, and
otherwise I feel pretty good.

875
01:07:01,851 --> 01:07:05,146
- I'm fine. Don't baby me.
- Just drink it.

876
01:07:06,063 --> 01:07:08,899
- Hey, Shogo!
- Huh?

877
01:07:15,573 --> 01:07:18,701
[SCREAM OF RAGE]

878
01:07:37,178 --> 01:07:41,265
What'd you expect? That I'd stand there?
That's not how this world works!

879
01:07:41,348 --> 01:07:45,227
Right doesn't make
might, understand?

880
01:07:46,062 --> 01:07:49,482
Stand up, Yahagi!
Get on your feet!

881
01:07:51,150 --> 01:07:55,154
Why do you bastards... always
think you can look down on us?

882
01:07:55,696 --> 01:07:57,740
Is it because you're older?

883
01:07:57,823 --> 01:08:02,161
Is that what it is? Just because you're
strong, you can do anything...?

884
01:08:02,244 --> 01:08:06,332
Destroy everything? If you're strong,
that makes it right?!

885
01:08:07,374 --> 01:08:09,126
Well this is the result.

886
01:08:09,293 --> 01:08:12,088
That's it? That's all you got?

887
01:08:16,634 --> 01:08:21,931
Would there be any point?
It's all just a waste of time!

888
01:08:22,098 --> 01:08:24,850
[TWANGING VIBRATION]

889
01:08:36,362 --> 01:08:39,907
That's ADAM, the Moon's
defense system.

890
01:08:39,990 --> 01:08:43,369
The entire Moon is
one giant weapon.

891
01:08:59,802 --> 01:09:02,012
And that is Dezalg.

892
01:09:02,096 --> 01:09:05,057
The enemy that we've
been fighting.

893
01:09:43,387 --> 01:09:45,389
[HAPPY POP MUSIC]

894
01:10:09,914 --> 01:10:17,914
By the light of the stars
coming through the window...

895
01:10:18,547 --> 01:10:26,096
I gauge the distance
between the two of us.

896
01:10:26,180 --> 01:10:34,180
Feeling around, I fear your lips.

897
01:10:40,611 --> 01:10:48,611
Though I couldn't make a sound...

898
01:10:49,161 --> 01:10:56,835
I tried calling out your name.

899
01:10:56,919 --> 01:11:02,967
~i~Somewhere inside me...~b~
- And I guess this ship's next? - Perhaps.

900
01:11:03,384 --> 01:11:07,846
But where there's life, there's hope.
You can never give up.

901
01:11:11,183 --> 01:11:19,183
What can the two of us do for love?

902
01:11:22,194 --> 01:11:25,948
- I want you to tell us.
~b~- And a new age begins.~i~

903
01:11:26,115 --> 01:11:27,491
You're not scared?

904
01:11:27,658 --> 01:11:31,328
The world that we had was
one worth living for.

905
01:11:31,412 --> 01:11:32,746
[SIGHS]

906
01:11:32,830 --> 01:11:36,208
However, the time when I could live
as I thought was right has ended...

907
01:11:36,292 --> 01:11:38,210
at least for now.

908
01:11:42,381 --> 01:11:46,844
And the truth is that I envy all
of you for what will come.

909
01:11:48,637 --> 01:11:53,809
Shogo Yahagi, it's not likely
that we two will meet again.

910
01:11:56,353 --> 01:11:58,939
B.D....

911
01:12:01,817 --> 01:12:04,862
A pig-headed showoff
until the very end.

912
01:12:08,615 --> 01:12:16,615
The way you always smiled at me...

913
01:12:17,207 --> 01:12:24,173
I could not tell you how
clumsy it made me feel.

914
01:12:24,840 --> 01:12:30,763
Because it made you seem so far away...

915
01:12:30,846 --> 01:12:33,849
it made me feel lonely.

916
01:12:39,188 --> 01:12:47,188
I want the two of us to find
words of passion for love.

917
01:12:54,495 --> 01:13:01,293
Don't forget love.

918
01:13:01,377 --> 01:13:09,377
Please give me a dream-like secret.

919
01:13:17,434 --> 01:13:25,434
What can the two of us do for love?

920
01:13:28,445 --> 01:13:32,658
I want you to tell me.

921
01:13:32,741 --> 01:13:39,540
Don't let go of love.

922
01:13:39,623 --> 01:13:47,623
Please give me a dream-like secret.

923
01:13:48,048 --> 01:13:56,048
I want the two of us to find
passionate words of love.

924
01:14:03,355 --> 01:14:11,355
Please don't forget love...

925
01:15:09,087 --> 01:15:11,215
Is everyone OK?

926
01:15:11,381 --> 01:15:12,591
It's quiet.

927
01:15:12,758 --> 01:15:16,220
It's just a matter of time...
even in here.

928
01:15:16,386 --> 01:15:18,555
Well, if we're gonna die...

929
01:15:18,639 --> 01:15:22,935
I'd rather do it someplace where there's
enough light to see the faces of my friends.

930
01:15:45,374 --> 01:15:48,252
[GASPS]

931
01:15:48,335 --> 01:15:50,420
Yui!

932
01:15:54,049 --> 01:15:56,051
Shogo!

933
01:16:04,476 --> 01:16:06,895
Hey... are your wounds
hurting you?

934
01:16:07,062 --> 01:16:10,148
No, they're all completely healed.

935
01:16:15,862 --> 01:16:19,449
So, were you able to see Eve?

936
01:16:19,616 --> 01:16:22,703
Yeah, and she told me something.

937
01:16:22,786 --> 01:16:26,123
To grow up like the adults
I used to admire as a kid.

938
01:16:26,290 --> 01:16:30,669
- [GENTLE SCOFF] You?
- Yeah. It's a bit late now.

939
01:16:44,933 --> 01:16:52,933
~b~[A cappella]~i~ By the light of
the stars coming through the window...

940
01:16:54,318 --> 01:17:02,318
